    <!-- Touch monitoring info dialog -->
    <string name="info_dialog_touch"><![CDATA[The touch is valid when the display of Mi Band 2 changes (so it is advisable to rotate your wrist before touching).
        <p>It monitors elapsed time between touches, not the elapsed time to first touch.</p>
        <p>If you do just one touch, then that function will be always recognized.
           If you want to use more features, you\'ll need at least two touch or more with different timings.</p>
        <p>Green icons on the cards indicates which another function can be similar to current pattern.</p>
        <p>When you have an incoming call the device does not recognise the following functions in order to ease touch input: location of the device, repeat notifications, music control.</p>
        <p>In test mode does not execute the function of recognized pattern.</p>
        <p>Mi Band 2 vibration feedback just only, if there is a pattern taking into account the current status of the device (call answering, rejecting only if there is an incoming call…).</p>
        <p>Mi Band 2 vibrates once, when recognize a pattern.</p>
        <p>Mi Band 2 vibrates twice, when not recognize any pattern after the longest pattern (if <i>Not recognisable touch pattern signal</i> is set).</p>
    ]]></string>

